adviseScripts.text: Mister, even I feel like you don't take good care of yourself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Where'd you get the confidence to be like this?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: From you.
I'm just confident in myself.
Very well. I asked that question to hear this answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: That's why you have to stay by my side.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: If anyone dares to mess with you, I'll make them disappear without a trace.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: It's good that you're confident.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: But I hate it when my possessions have flaws.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: So, you should take better care of yourself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I spend a peaceful counseling session with Rosanna.
Another traitor turned up in the organization.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: They know that if they're caught, they'll pay with their lives, but they keep popping up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Sounds exhausting.
Sounds like lonely work.
It is, physically speaking, at least.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: In order to send a message, I usually take care of these things personally.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Once we're done here, I'll take care of this latest mole we found.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Lonely?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'm with you, Mister. Why would I be lonesome?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: We usually weed out these moles before I have time to get emotionally attached to them anyway.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: During our session, Rosanna and I talk about traitors.
Your room is a bit barebone, Mister.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: How about decorating it a little more?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Think I should upgrade the chairs?
Think I should get a fancier carpet?
Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Don't you think it'd be somewhat weird only having one top-of-the-line chair?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: If that's what you're after, though, I won't stop you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I think that'd help the vibe in here. I approve.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: What do you think about having it in black and white?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I like neutral colors.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a discussion about interior design with Rosanna.
If someone hit you without provocation,
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: what would you do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'd call the A.C.P.U.
I'd hit them right back.
Right... I suppose you live in a world governed by rules.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: But if there ever comes a time when someone's in your face, feel free to give them a smack.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'll take care of the rest.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: A perfect answer. For me, that is.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'm not so sure about you, though.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: The world you live in is different from mine. Yours is governed by rules.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Don't feel as if you have to impress me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a short counseling session with Rosanna.
I'm sorry, but I think I'll have to cut today's session short.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: ... Duck!
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Duck at once.
Try to figure out what's going on first.
*Bang bang*
I didn't think they'd follow me all the way out here.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Sorry for startling you. Let me take care of this real quick.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You idiot!
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Rosanna forcefully pushes my head down.
*Bang bang*
When you're with me, act first, ask questions later.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: If not, you're only making it harder to protect you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a dangerous counseling session with Rosanna.
I feel like having a bit of the strong stuff.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Got any booze around here?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: All I've got is soda.
How about we go out for a drink after our session?
Soda...
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Not really my thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'd prefer something with a little more kick.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Hey now, where'd this impulsiveness come from?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'm down.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'll get a table at the place I usually go to.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation about alcohol with Rosanna.
Ugh... I'm bored.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Is there anything fun to do around here?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You could look for someone worth killing.
We could play a board game.
You think I roam the streets looking for people to kill whenever I'm bored?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'm not perfect, but I'm not a psychopath.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: ... I suppose doing that would help alleviate my boredom though...
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You've got board games? That sounds fun.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: What kind of games do you have?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Be forewarned: I'm super competitive.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I kill some time with Rosanna during an uneventful counseling session.
The guy I was supposed to make a deal with didn't show up yesterday.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I've been dealing with him for quite some time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: If you were in this situation, Mister, what would you be thinking?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: That there must have been some reason that he wasn't able to make it.
That he'd betrayed me.
Oh, you sweet summer child.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: In our world, your word is your bond.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Unless he's dead in a ditch somewhere, there's no excuse for him not showing up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: To do otherwise is considered a betrayal, plain and simple.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Correct.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: If there was a genuine reason that he couldn't show up, he would have found a way to notify me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: He's been covering his tracks, so I think he's up to something.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: We plan on finding him within two days.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Betrayal is not something we take lightly, nor should you, Mister.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation about a heavy topic with Rosanna.
Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: So handsome.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'd appreciate it if you stopped staring.
I already know that I'm handsome.
Are you doing that on purpose?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You know telling me something will only make me want to do the opposite.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Soooo, I'll take that to mean you want me to stare even more.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Talking like that is kind of a buzzkill, even for you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Don't take it personally, that's just how I feel.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation about appearance with Rosanna.
Moran has really been pushing it lately.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I feel like my patience is quickly running thin.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Any ideas on how I can handle her?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'll talk to her.
Why don't you try talking to her nicely?
If you could, that'd be great.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: If I tried talking to her,
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: a war might break out.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Talk nicely?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: To HER?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Please tell me you're joking.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation about Moran with Rosanna.
Rosanna doesn't seem to be in a good mood.
At times like this, it's best to...
Stay quiet.
Try talking.
What are you doing?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You can clearly see that I'm in a foul mood, and you're just going to stand there gawking at me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have to say,
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: hearing your voice does make me feel a bit better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Keep talking.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: It doesn't matter what about.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I continue counseling Rosanna while trying to make her feel better.
*Bang*
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Argh!
*Bang bang*
No good. If this was for real, you'd be pushing up daisies.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Good acting, though.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Very nice!
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Paying back one shot with two.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: If this was real, I would have lost.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Rosanna and I continue acting out various scenarios during our session.
I'm curious about what people think about Hedonia.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: What do you think?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: They probably fear you.
They probably consider you a sort of rag-tag family.
That's fine with me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: With fear comes power.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: The greater the fear, the fewer people there will be giving me guff.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: So you'd do well to stick close to me, Mister.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Don't you think that's taking us just a tad too lightly?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You make it sound like people don't fear us at all.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation about Hedonia with Rosanna.
I'm curious about something.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: What scares you more: a knife or a gun?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Knife.
Gun.
I figured as much.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: People seem to fear knives more because they're so accessible.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: It's easier to imagine what it'd be like to get cut with one.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: In that case, I'll subject my next target to the tip of a knife.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Hmm. You've been around your fair share of guns, so I suppose it makes sense that you'd feel that way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Most people have a greater fear of knives.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: The vast majority of people haven't been shot before, so it's probably harder for them to imagine the pain of a gunshot.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: So, I actually think I should torture my next target with a knife instead.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a somewhat unnerving conversation with Rosanna.
I heard you went to see cherry blossoms with Sakura a while back.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Where do you plan on taking me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: The shopping mall.
The hotel.
Shopping mall?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Is there something you've been wanting to buy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I could buy it for you, no problem, but I have to say, I'm a little disappointed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I was thinking you'd take me somewhere special.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'll take that as a signal, and an obvious one at that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I'll take you up on that offer!
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: What time works best for you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I make date plans with Rosanna.
Mister.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: If you had to choose between the head or heart, which would it be?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Head.
Heart.
A wise decision.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Regardless of whether it's a Nikke or a human, aim for the head.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: That's the only way you'll stay alive.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text:
The heart isn't a bad idea, 
but that'll pose problems if you're going up against a Nikke.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: So make a habit of aiming for the head.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: My eyes are up here, Mister.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Rosanna and I have an agreeable counseling session.
Rosanna is aiming a gun at me.
This is the end, Mister.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Any last words?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I-I'm sorry I never got to see the surface!
S-save me!
Aw, how cute.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: *Pop*
A flower comes out of Rosanna's gun.
A present from the surface.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Scaredy-cat.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: *Pop*
A flower comes out of Rosanna's gun.
Why were you so scared? I've always treated you well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a counseling session with Rosanna that nearly gives me a heart attack.
*Tap tap*
Rosanna taps her lips twice with her fingers.
Lean in closer to Rosanna.
Tap your own lips twice.
Hmm?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: That's not what I was hinting at.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You need to learn to read signals better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Having said that... you can continue what you were doing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You're pretty good at reading signals.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: This is a secret signal I use often.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: It means that the person in front of me can be trusted.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: So, it's clear that we can trust each other more than ever.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I have a meaningful counseling session with Rosanna.
*Phew* I'm pooped.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Can I rest a little?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Of course.
Did something happen?
Man, this couch is comfy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: It's not easy for me to let my guard down around others.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Thanks, Mister.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Nothing out of the ordinary.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You shouldn't ask too many questions.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: You might get hurt if you know too much.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: I spend a while watching Rosanna rest.
I'm thinking of buying some new clothes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: What do you think would look good on me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Bright colors that pop.
Subtle, neutral colors.
Is that what you like?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Well, it doesn't suit me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: If I wore garish clothing, I'd attract a lot of unwanted attention, which would make my life more difficult than it already is.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Good call.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: It's better for me to fly under the radar, so I usually go for inconspicuous colors.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: They tend to look better on me, anyway.
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: How about we go shopping?
adviseScripts.speaker: Rosanna

adviseScripts.text: Rosanna and I spend some time thinking about what clothes she could buy.
